is a=20
                              software architecture that separates an=20
                              application's data model, user interface, =
and=20
                              control logic into three distinct =
components so=20
                              that modifications to one component can be =
made=20
                              with minimal impact to the others. MVC is =
often=20
                              thought of as a software design pattern. =
However,=20
                              MVC encompasses more of the architecture =
of an=20
                              application than is typical for a design =
pattern.=20
                              Hence the term architectural pattern may =
be useful=20
                              (Buschmann, et al 1996), or perhaps an =
aggregate=20
                              design pattern."<BR><BR>In this article, =
we are=20
                              enforcing rules of robustness analysis on =
the=20
                              enterprise architecture. So the =
architecture that=20
                              is presented here uses the policies/rules =
we have=20
                              defined earlier during our analysis and =
applied it=20
                              on to Model-View-Architecture. I dont know =
if MVP=20
                              (model-view-presenter) do the same thing. =
If it is=20
                              then you may call it MVP pattern. Also i =
wanted to=20
                              add one more thing that MVP from Fowler is =
no=20
                              more, actually he has divided into two =
patterns -=20
                              Supervising Controller and Passive View. =
